  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Christiania is on a half-board basis.</p>
<p>Each morning a varied continental buffet breakfast with additional hot options is served between 7 - 9.30am</p>
<p>A served four course a la carte evening meal with choice of menu is served between 7.30-9.45pm</p>
<p>Christmas and New Year gala dinners included</p>
<p>Earlier meal times for children are available from 6pm (on request)</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>One of the resort’s leading hotels, the Christiania exudes luxury and elegance and is renowned for excellent service and cuisine. You will find a relaxed atmosphere as well as a warm welcome from the hotel team. Enjoying a prime location in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/16c56b283bca4ae2b2ada820a5d3a03d" href="/{localLink:umb://document/16c56b283bca4ae2b2ada820a5d3a03d}" title="Val d'Isere">Val d'Isère</a>, the vibrant centre and nearest lifts are only a snowballs throw away. Take the time to relax at the end of a hard day skiing in the superb spa with indoor pool, sauna and Turkish bath.</p>
<h2>Central location</h2>
<p>With a central location in <a data-udi="umb://document/16c56b283bca4ae2b2ada820a5d3a03d" href="/{localLink:umb://document/16c56b283bca4ae2b2ada820a5d3a03d}" title="Val d'Isere">Val D'Isere</a> you are close to the lively resort centre where you can find a variety of different shops, bars and restaurants. The slopes are just a minute away so you can easily get on and off the mountain each day, making this an excellent choice for the keen skiers and snowboarders. </p>
<h2>Soothing spa and relaxation</h2>
<p><span>‍The hotel has a lovely spa and wellness area available for you to use after a day on the slopes. Facilities include an indoor swimming pool, sauna and hammam, and for the ultimate treat you can book a massage or beauty treatment with the beauty therapists.  </span></p>
<h2>Food and drink</h2>
<p><span>The Hotel Christiania bar is the perfect spot to catch up with family and friends, with plenty of seating and a large fireplace it is a lovely area to enjoy a snack and a cocktail too. </span><span>Half board meals are taken the the cosy restaurant with wonderful mountain views, each day you can enjoy breakfast and dinner both made with local produce. Breakfast includes a varied hot and cold buffet with a range of regional produce, and evening meals include a starter, main course, cheese board and dessert.</span></p>
<h2>Family friendly</h2>
<p>The hotel hosts its own kids club throughout the French school holidays <span>for children aged 5 to 10.</span> The little ones can join in a <span>variety of games and activities designed by the entertainment team including games, arts and crafts, and workshops. This gives the adults time to relax in peace at the spa or bar.<br /></span></p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
