  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>North Facing Rooms</strong> are around 20m² sleeping two people. These rooms have village views and can be affected by exterior noise. </p>
<p><strong>West Facing Rooms</strong> are around 22m² sleeping two people. These rooms are larger, with views of the village and Face de Bellevarde. These rooms may be affected by exterior noise. </p>
<p><strong>South Facing Rooms</strong> are around 24m² sleeping two people with twin beds, with a balcony or terrace with <span>South facing across the snow front and Vallée du Manchet. These rooms are on request, please give our Reservations team a call to book. </span></p>
<p><strong>Double Superior Rooms</strong> are around 26m²  sleeping two to four people with a double bed, and bunk beds in the entranceway. These rooms have views of the ice-rink, <span>Vallée du Fornet, and Massif de Solaise. </span>Please note that if booking for two people then a room without the cabin will be provided.</p>
<p>Single occupancy rooms (with a supplement) and interconnecting rooms are available on request.</p>
<p><strong>Room facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>All rooms have twin or double beds (please specify preference when booking)</li>
<li>Mountain views</li>
<li>Satellite TV with English speaking channels</li>
<li>DVD player</li>
<li>Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Tea and coffee making facilities (on request)</li>
<li>Bathrobe and slippers</li>
<li>Telephone</li>
<li>Radio</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Toiletries </li>
<li>Bath with shower head attachment</li>
<li>WC</li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
